text.section:
When a district has filed a proceeding to condemn land or any interest therein or personal property, pursuant to the provisions of the Eminent Domain Act of Kentucky, and the board of such district shall determine that the necessity for procuring possession of the property is urgent, it may pass a resolution, at the time that said condemnation is authorized or at any time thereafter for a declaration of taking, declaring that said lands are to be taken for the use of a metropolitan sewer district. Said declaration of taking shall contain, or have annexed thereto, the following:
A statement of the authority under which and, the public use for which, said lands are taken;
A description of the lands taken sufficient for identification thereof;
A statement of the estate or interest in said lands taken for said public use;
A plat showing the lands taken.
